  
**Downloading the CSL Air Quality Sensor (AQS) Code from GitHub**

**Step I. Using GitHub** 

The Community Sensor Lab’s DIY Air Monitoring files include instructions on assembling and operating the air quality monitor. The files can be accessed on GitHub using the link below\! 

Visit:  [Community Sensor Lab](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab)  ↓

[GitHub](https://github.com/) is an online platform where code is stored, shared, and collaboratively worked on. You **don't** need a GitHub account to visit the site or download the code. 

You can access our files by following the instructions on The Community Sensor Lab's GitHub page\! 

Visit:  [Community Sensor Lab](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab)  ↓ 

1. Go to the **Repositories** drop-down menu.  
     
2. Find and click on Air-Quality-Sensor.

---

**Step II. Air-Quality-Sensor Repository**  

3. Once the [Air Quality Sensor Repository](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab/Air-Quality-Sensor) opens, it will display all the folders in the file.

4. The first folder, [CSL-AQS-V2.1](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab/Air-Quality-Sensor/tree/master/CSL-AQS-V4), has all the code you need to run your Air Quality Sensor.

5. The '[Images](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab/Air-Quality-Sensor/tree/master/images)' folder contains all the images referenced in the [README.md file](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab/Air-Quality-Sensor/blob/master/README.md), including instructions and additional information about AQS.

6. The file [wifi\_logger\_proto.gs](https://github.com/Community-Sensor-Lab/Air-Quality-Sensor/blob/master/wifi_logger_proto.gs) contains code for connecting the sensor to Google Sheets. 

**Step III. Downloading Code** 

7. It will prompt a couple of options on the menu bar. Under HTTPS, scroll down and select Download Zip.

                                                           

                                                               

8. Click on Download ZIP. Once the download is complete, click on the Air-Quality-Sensor-master.zip file. A blue folder named Air-Quality-Sensor-master will appear. If you’re using Windows, follow the standard procedure to extract files.  
      
9. Save this folder in a location where you can easily find it again.   
     
10. Open the zip file. Once the blue folder appears, you can delete the zip file.

11.  The Air-Quality-Sensor-master has several folders; you will only need the  CSL-AQS-V2.1 folder.   
      
12. **Delete** the images, README.md, and wifi\_logger\_proto.gs. folders.

**Step IV. Installing Arduino** 

Instructions for Installing Arduino IDE:

1. Visit the Arduino website: [https://www.arduino.cc/en/software](https://www.arduino.cc/en/software)  
2. Scroll down and select the download version compatible with your operating system: Windows, macOS, or Linux.  
3. Follow the installation prompts based on your system.  
4. Once installed, open the Arduino IDE to confirm it's working correctly.

---

**Running the Code in the Arduino Microcontroller**

**![alt text](../images/CSL_Air_Quality_Sensor_AQS_GitHub1.JPG)**  
To open the code in Arduino, select File→Open and select the downloaded  CSL-AQS-(insert version) folder. 

Before **compiling** and **uploading** the code, check the **Board Name** so that it reads (Adafruit Feather M0 (SAMD21) and the **Port** should also have the same name as the Board (Adafruit Feather M0 (SAMD21).

For the board:

Select Tools \> Board \> Adafruit SAMD Boards \> Adafruit Feather M0

![alt text](../images/CSL_Air_Quality_Sensor_AQS_GitHub2.JPG)

For the Port Connection: 

Select Tools \> Port \> (Sensor Name) \[Ex: Adafruit Feather M0\] \- Matches the Adafruit Feather M0 name (SAMD21).

![alt text](../images/CSL_Air_Quality_Sensor_AQS_GitHub3.JPG)

After reviewing the code, use the two buttons on the left side of the **Tool Bar**  (check mark ✔ and right arrow ➔). The check mark ✔ will **Compile** the sketch and the right arrow ➔ will **Upload** the code.

![alt text](../images/CSL_Air_Quality_Sensor_AQS_GitHub4.JPG)

**Provisioning the WiFi and Google Sheet credentials**

This step connects the system to the available Wi-Fi network (it must be a standard Wi-Fi network). 

The code will have to go through provisioning (setup). During this step, connect your phone to the AQS system's Wi-Fi network, which will be displayed on the OLED screen. 

The steps required for this are:

* Connect to the AQS systems' WiFi network.  
    
* Access the internet and go to [https://192.168.1.1/](https://192.168.1.1/)  
    
* Enter your Wi-Fi network and password, and then select ‘Submit’.
